rungsprozesse und Geschlechterordnungen die Sicht auf Gefühle von Schwangeren prägen.  aWhether it is mood swings or motherly love during pregnancy - hormones often serve as the explanation and are identified as the cause of such phenomena. At the same time, the idea that negative emotions such as stress impair somatic processes is also widespread. In her historic analysis, Lisa Malich addresses the correlation between conceptions of emotions and models of the body for the first time. Using self-help literature and scientific texts on pregnancy from the late 18th century to today, she shows how processes of medicalization and gender hierarchies shape views on the feelings of pregnant women.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aPregnancyxPsychological aspects. 4aEmotionsgeschichte. 4aGefühle. 4aGender Studies. 4aGender. 4aGeschichtswissenschaft. 4aGeschlechtergeschichte. 4aGeschlechterordnung. 4aHormone. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aKörper. 4aKörpermodelle. 4aMedikalisierung. 4aMedizin. 4aMedizingeschichte. 4aMutterschaft. 4aRatgeberliteratur. 4aWissensgeschichte. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aBody Models.  aBody.  aCultural History.  aEmotions.  aGender History.  aGender Order.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aGuidebooks.  aHistory of Emotions.  aHistory of Knowledge.  aHistory of Medicine.  aHistory.  aHormones.  aMedicalization.  aMedicine.  aMotherhood.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2017z9783110547764oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839435960zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyte